entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what is your dream job

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: my dream job would actually be traveling around the world and having a show on like the travel channel that would be my dream job because i would get paid to travel and it is something i enjoy to do doing so i would love to do that as a job

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: sometimes when i am feeling tense i turn on the fish tank screensaver hey i know it is not hawaii but it is the best i have got what do you do to relax

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i love reading and i love taking baths so to relax i like to take a bath and i read while i am in the bath and i also like going to the gym that helps me deal with stress and it actually relaxes me even though i am exercising

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is great how are you at controlling your temper

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i used to be not very good at controlling it when i was a kid i would get mad very easily and sometimes as an adult i still get angry easily but i have gotten a lot better at trying to think about things first before saying them and not having outbursts things like that

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: when was the last time you argued with someone and what was it about

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: the last time i argued with somebody was probably about a week ago it was my best friend and she actually she has kids i do not and for some reason she thought or thinks that i think i am a better person than she is and because i went to school and she did not and she is home with kids and you know i am able to do more things i do not think i have ever made her feel that i i and i definitely know i do not feel like i am better than her but for some reason she accused me of that and we had an argent about it

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: yeah tell me about a situation that you wish you had handled differently

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: well that situation i wish i had handled differently because when she was talking to me she was very upset and i started off pretty calm just trying to reason with her and let her know that i certaintly did not feel like i was better than her but towards the end of the conversation it just kinda turned into a yelling match between the two of us and i wish i had been able to just stay calm and maybe asked her to call me later once we calmed down instead of just continuing the argent

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: h how did you feel in that moment

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i was angry at first but once we hung up i felt really bad about the situation i felt that maybe i could have just let her let out all her feelings and then try to speak to her calmly instead of yelling at her too

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i see what you mean tell me about the hardest decision you have ever had to make

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: oh wow that is a tough one i think gosh i think one of the toughest hardest decisions i have had to make is breaking up with a boyfriend of seven years although i knew that it was the right thing to do i was kind of hanging on to the fact that we had been together for so many years and i kinda felt by ending the relationship i would have wasted those last seven years of my life it was a pretty tough decision to make but i realized that it was the best decision for me at the time and i am actually glad i did because then i went on to meet my husband

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: aw

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is great

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: thank you

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: tell me about an event or something that you wish you could erase from your memory

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: well about i would say maybe fifteen years ago i was hanging out with a couple of friends at a club and they met some guys and they invited us back to their place and i really did not wanna go because i did not know these people and i mean i knew their names and that is about it but my friends really wanted to go and i was not the one driving so i decided to just go along with them and back at their house one of the guys actually pulled me into a room and tried i i got scared i yelled he tried to choke me and i thought i was gonna die right right there i thought he was gonna kill me but luckily one of my friends knocked on the door because she heard me scream and we left so it could have been a worse situation but i still think about it and wish that i could erase it from my mind

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: yeah that sounds really hard

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: it was

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: tell me about your relationship with your family

entries.text: we have a pretty good relationship i am close to i have a sister and a brother my sister is two years younger and my brother is two years older and we get along pretty well my sister and i used to be best friends but then we grew apart and then now we are actually closer i think than ever and i have a pretty good relationship with my parents my dad still treats me like i am a little kid sometimes which annoys me

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: laughter

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: but i think we have a pretty good solid relationship

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is good

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yeah

entries.text: how easy is it for you to get a good night is sleep

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i usually wake up a few times throughout the night so i think it is rare for me to sleep the whole night through ever and i do feel a little like tired in the morning when i wake up it is hard i am not a morning person definitely so yeah it is kinda hard to get a good night is sleep

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: why

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i do not know it i have a hard time falling asleep and then sometimes i have bad dreams or i need to get up to use the restroom but yeah it i do not remember the last time i actually slept the whole night without waking up at least once

entries.text: how have you been feeling lately

entries.text: emotionally good i am actually on vacation right now from work so that is really nice physically i feel good i have not been to the gym in a while so that kinda makes me feel bad cause i like working out but health wise i am good
